"{\"abstract\":\"We study the proportional chore division problem where a protocol wants to divide an undesirable object, called chore, among $n$ different players. The goal is to find an allocation such that the cost of the chore assigned to each player be at most $1/n$ of the total cost. This problem is the dual variant of the cake cutting problem in which we want to allocate a desirable object. Edmonds and Pruhs showed that any protocol for the proportional cake cutting must use at least $\\\\Omega(n \\\\log n)$ queries in the worst case, however, finding a lower bound for the proportional chore division remained an interesting open problem. We show that chore division and cake cutting problems are closely related to each other and provide an $\\\\Omega(n \\\\log n)$ lower bound for chore division.\",\"arxivId\":\"1710.00271\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"144164080\",\"name\":\"A. Farhadi\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144164080\"},{\"authorId\":\"1704161\",\"name\":\"M. Hajiaghayi\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1704161\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"30870661\",\"name\":\"Y. Okano\"},{\"authorId\":\"34879375\",\"name\":\"Y. Manabe\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"eaea8cfded6223a140684b313a7aa500c76d999d\",\"title\":\"A three-player envy-free division protocol for mixed manna\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/eaea8cfded6223a140684b313a7aa500c76d999d\",\"venue\":\"\",\"year\":2018},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"30870661\",\"name\":\"Y. Okano\"},{\"authorId\":\"34879375\",\"name\":\"Y. Manabe\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1007/978-3-030-63000-3_4\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"e2da79bad28807cf79d19c4b3ca2388fee57efbb\",\"title\":\"A Three-Player Envy-Free Discrete Division Protocol for Mixed Manna\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/e2da79bad28807cf79d19c4b3ca2388f